Had so much fun shooting the other day so here’s a little montage of what we managed to capture at golden hour. Enjoy & don’t forget to get out and move your body today!

💕SAVE & TRY💕
4 movements to STRETCH & STRENGTHEN YOUR CORE! 
Functional movements babyyy🤩
Complete each movement for a minute! EMOM style!

1.Crunch Arch
let your back arch. Then, as you crunch reach the hand up towards the sky, no further than your shoulders.

2.Rainbow side plank! 
Lower your hips as close to the earth while driving your elbow into your side, body. THEN Keep your hips ultra lifted as you reach your arm towards the earth. Your shoulders can twist toward the floor! 

3.Three Part Oblique leg extension 
Your hand and your knee are in the same line. As the hips lower, they also reach back from the lift up, extending the leg as far out and up as possible, and squeeze the knee into the chest and repeat.

4.Side Plank Tap  to Wild thing 
The slower you move the better. Try to move with precision and mindfulness, each round sneaking in a lovely little backbend to stretch the back and the belly. 

Let me know how these movement feel in your body! Stay sweaty my friends 
Wearing @aloyoga 
🎥 & edit by @josemarth

💃🏽HIIT Booty BLASTER!!!💃🏽
Explosive movements that SCULPT your glutes!
Complete every movement for as many repetitions AS POSSIBLE! Go until failure💦 Do as many as you possibly can, and then do five more because you got this! Take little rest in between movements- about 30 seconds!
Your heart & booty will thank you 🙏🏽 

Fun fact:
These explosive movements are working your type 2 muscle fibers! That means, if you’re a weightlifter like me, these moments are going to help your weightlifting AND your weightlifting will support your explosive movements 🙌🏽 HIIT workout & weightlifting work your fast twitch muscle fibers! Let’s see what they are capable of and get STRONG beautiful well shaped muscles y’all!! 

1.Jump squats! 
-Explode from the very bottom of your squat! 

2.180 degree jump squats 
-Drive up through your heels rotating from side to side.

3.Jump lunges
-Explode from the bottom y’all! Build that booty! And don’t stop until failure! Until you truly can’t do any more. 

4.Super Mario
-Spring up as high as possible, and then reload with the same leg! Count your repetitions so you can do the same amount on each side.

You should be completely drained by the end! 
This is a total torture for the glutes! 
Let me know how it goes(: 
Stay sweaty my friends 🫶🏽

🍑4 booty workouts to lift & sculpt that A$$🍑
Save & Try 
Resistance Booty EMOM
EMOM: Every minute on the minute 
These are lifting and sculpting movements for the BOOTY BABY make sure you do both sides 🫶🏽 

1.Resistance split lunge:
Band around the bottom of the foot and in the corresponding hand. Hinge forward slightly to target the booty keeping the spine straight.

2.Deep Squat + lateral toe tap
As you squat act like you’re ducking a rope, getting as low as possible, keeping the knee, super wide!
Add that lateral toe tap at the end, holding a squat position on the standing leg.

3.Triple Squat Pulse 
Keep a nice deep squad as you lean forward slightly while pulsing the knees out wide.
(Make sure you do both sides) 

4.Banded single leg Bridge 
Band goes UNDER the bottom foot and OVER the top foot! 
This one will really get your booty fired up! 

Complete the circuit 3X and let me know how it goes(:

🏋🏽‍♀️Weighted BOOTY LIFT 🏋🏽‍♀️
SAVE & TRY
Your booty with thank you 
& you can thank me later 😉

1.Donkey Kick Hold + Tricep Tap
10 Times! 
Keep the weight AND knee as HIGH as humanly possible throughout this entire movement! Go as slow as possible too!! Doing these two things will make it a whole lot harder and lift your booty a whole lot higher!! 

2.PULSES!! 
Straight back 
5X SLOWLY 
At a diagonal 
5X EVEN SLOWER 
Out to the side 
5X THE SLOWEST 

3.Cross Body Donkey Kick 
10 times
Similar to a normal donkey kick, on the way down make sure you are crossing the knee with the weight outside of the supporting knee. 
Pulse 10 times 

4.Double Pulse Bridge 
10 times 
Keep the core super engaged so as you lift your hips up and slowly lower, your spine does not move and your glutes are doing all the work. Make sure that you double pulse at the top thinking about engaging the glutes.

5.Tippy Toe Double Bridge 
10 times 
Same rules apply as a number 4 

Pulse 
10 times

6.Bound Angle Bridge 
The blade edges of your feet are down as your feet squeeze together. Denise stay wide the entire time as you left the heads up and slowly lower. This is a great way to involve different muscles in the glutes.
Pulse 10 times at the top 

REPEAT this entire sequence 3 times!

Save & Try

💚Save & Try💚 
Try on these hip mobility movements!! 
They feel SO yummy 🤤 
 You’ll thank me later (; 

1.Mini Warrior Two Pulses 
Option to lift your heel  or added engagement 
Bend deeply into your front knee 
Keep your knee driving towards your pinky toe engaging your BOOTY baby
Keep your posture nice and straight the entire time. 

2.Half Straddle Childs Pose
The leg in straddle stays straight the ENTIRE time! The straighter the better. 
Lift your leg high as possible 
As you sit into child’s pose, take your time and marinate there for a breath in between movements.

3.Supine 3 Part Knee Circles 
Keeping your spine glued to the earth, slowly circle your leg while encouraging your knee as wide as possible.

4.Resisted Butterfly
Press your hands into your knees!! Press your knees into hands!! Lots of pressure the entire time as you work your knees up & down SLOWLY. 
Resisting on the way up and down to ACTIVELY stretch! 

Go for an entire minute on each side for each movement. You can cycle through all for movements as many times as possible. If you are dealing with lower back and or hip pain, this would be an incredibly helpful series to do every day.

Let me know how your body feels after! Happy stretching!

I am slowly, but surely, gaining my strength back after breaking my foot! 
I am so damn lucky to get to workout with @giorgiomerlino he has completely changed the way that I train 🙏🏽

I challenge my body with resistance training so that my bones adapt by becoming denser and stronger! Hopefully preventing suture fractures.😅 Aaaaaand for the booty gains 🤑

This particular session we accidentally worked on drop setting weights because my grip strength isn’t what it was. 

Progressively reducing the weight as you continue your sets allows your muscles to reach new levels of fatigue and recruitment. It’s a surefire way to maximize muscle fiber activation and hopefully grow a booty that has its own area code 😂🙃🤓

Here’s a fun/tricky pose to try out with a friend AND spotter! 

Save this demonstration of me & @tawnyjanae so you can try it out later🫶🏽

Acro tips:
Flyer: When loading into pigeon, make sure to grab onto the base’s foot & your own ankle. For extra stability you can keep your hands on your front ankle & knee. Be active throughout this pose and try not to sink your hips or bend the back leg. 

Base: have an external rotation, when stepping on the Flyers foot. Create a C-grip around ankle & knee. Make sure to stack your arms & the flyers leg before extending the the back/bent leg. IMPORTANT: When coming out, make sure to bring your free leg to the flyer so they can find stability when stepping down.

Use a spotter, this shape has the tendency of going sideways when falling. Have the spotter close to the flyer and hands around the waist. Safety first!

Have fun my friends! Big thanks to @josemarth for video credit 🙏🏽

Both wearing @aloyoga 🤸🏽‍♀️

Upper Body Mobility Workout💪🏽

Try these movements on to increase mobility & strength in your shoulder girdle!

1.Dolphin Nose Taps 
You can absolutely bend your knees if needed! 
When I first started incorporating these into my fitness in yoga practice, I can barely move forward a few inches so stay with it and you will see the progress in your body! 

2.Crossbody kick-out 
This is a very fun and effective move, take it slowly, and continuously encourage your shoulders away from your ears.

3.Bear to Plank 
This is a very simple move, but it is also wildly affect. If you can take this as slowly as quickly as you’d like maybe try both and let me know how it goes.

4.Tricep dip to L-sit 
If you are having any trouble getting your hips through your arms, you can always try this on to blocks!

Let me know how your body feels after trying on these movements!😻

Acro tips:
Flyer: When loading in, make sure to grab onto the base’s foot and lift both legs at the same time. Wrap the foot around the base’s arms. Be active throughout this pose and try not to sink your hips. 

Base: one hand will go underneath the hamstring close to the knee, and the other one toward the ankle. Make sure to stack both legs and arms. Check out the video to see the hand position underneath the knee. 
IMPORTANT: When coming out, make sure to bring your leg to the flyer so they can find stability when stepping down.

Use a spotter, this shape has the tendency of going backwards when falling. Have the spotter close to the flyer and hands around the waist. Safety first!

Here’s a fun post to try out with a friend! Save it for later 🙌🏽

ACRO HOW TO:

Flyers
1- start close to your base, and place your hands around the base’s wrist.

2 - when sitting, make sure to lean back onto the base fingers & their head

3 - slowly lift 1 foot off the floor and when you are stable, lift the other.

4 - make sure to sit up a little, keeping some weight on the base finger, feel free to create any pose that it’s comfortable for you. Remember to move slowly! 

Base
1 - start with sitting knees, shoulders distance apart.

2 - the hand placement should be a little bit above the butt, fingers making contact with the sacrum.

3 - feel free to lean in and use your head while getting into this position😉

4 - make sure to stack your arms to find ease in this balance.

Spotter
1 -  Stand next to the flyer with hands around the flyer’s waist & be on the ready! 

Let us know how it goes!

I’ve got friends in HIGH places BABY… & when I say “HIGH”… I mean it literally😝 
8,000 feet high to be exact 🤓😎
Lake tahoe is my favorite place on EARTH for so many reasons!!! 
The people & the winter season are just two of them. 
This was a wild winter week at an off-grid house in the backcountry only accessible by snowmobiles in the winder!! CRAZYYYY right?! 
This was back in 2022 with my friends out in Tahoe that are like family to me 🫶🏽
I had never ridden a snowmobile by myself before either so the adventure started immediately!!
It was just me & a lovely batch of humans who all had the right combination of bravery & stupidity 🤓❤️‍🔥😅
We had the time of our LIVES snowboarding & snowmobiling every damn day however/whenever we could. Which wasn’t particularly easy as the storms kept rolling in, trying to bury us alive whether we were inside or out 😝
But when you choose into every condition, every storm & every situation like it is an adventure perfectly designed JUST for you… life gets f*cking FUUUUUUN!! 
& then to top it all off if the collective mindset of the whole damn group has the same mindset… you’ve got yourself a pretty wicked adventure crew! 
That’s what this trip represented. 
The problems kept showing the f*ck up & SO did WE 😍 
Enjoy this cyber photo album of my experience last year. I hope it inspires you to get outside with friends and create lasting memories 🫶🏽❤️‍🔥🫶🏽
I am excited for WHATEVER this snow season has to offer. Let’s all make the most of what’s to come 💋
Namaste, 
  TJ

I’ve been a little MIA from more than a few areas of my life recently. 
I’ve been easing into a slower pace to allow myself space to tend to my heart🩶 
Grief is a funny thing. It’s as if all grief is tethered together by a golden thread.
A sparkly dainty looking string that is deceivingly strong.
So when I experience a new loss, it dredges up every past experience attached to that emotion. 
Or maybe this is just what healing is. 
Constant. Ever changing & never going away. 
A not so gentle reminder to make the most of our borrowed time inside these bodies we have been gifted. 
Honestly, I wouldn’t have it any other way because it makes me more present, more appreciative, more shameless in love & more aware of how finite this experience is. 
That heightened awareness makes me play full out in life. 
So fuck it. 
Here’s to grief, loss, pain & tears 🥂
On a lighter/more positive note…
I’m simultaneously feeling like the luckiest girl in the world 🥹 
My love @simonhill flew with me for 30 freaking hours from Australia to San Francisco & back to attend a funeral for someone he has never met. 
SIMPLY to support me 🥹🥹😭 To make sure I wouldn’t feel too sad or alone 🥹🥰😭
He is the only man to “meet” my Dad 
& we spent some giggly quality time with my mom 🫶🏽🫶🏽 @thelovelylori 🫶🏽🫶🏽
Life is beautiful 
Let’s savor every moment we have with the people we love 💗
